   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3661_1.jpg"/>
            <note type="letterhead">
               <hi rend="smallcaps">MELBURY, DORCHESTER.</hi><lb/>
               <seg>Station: <placeName>Yeovil Junction</placeName> (S.W.R.)</seg>; 
               <seg>Telegraph &amp; Parcels: <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2649837">Evershot</placeName> (G.W.R.).</seg>
            </note>
            <dateline>
               <date when="1912-03-02">March 2.</date>
               <lb/><placeName>Melbury</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2651101">Dorchester</placeName>.
            </dateline>
            <opener>
               <salute>Dear <persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/54148778">Mr. Hardy</persName>,</salute>
            </opener>
            
            <p>
               I have been waiting<lb/>
               to write to you until<lb/>
               the weather had im-<lb/>
               proved a little, &amp;<lb/>
               ask you when it<lb/>
               would suit you to<lb/>
               come
            </p>
            
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3661_2.jpg"/>
            
            <p>
               here &amp; spend a day<lb/>
               (if you will not<lb/>
               stay longer) &amp; see<lb/>
               the place. Would<lb/>
               Monday March 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi><lb/>
               suit you; or would you<lb/>
               prefer &amp; come a<lb/>
               little later on in<lb/>
               April?
            </p>
            
            <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3661_3.jpg"/>
            
            <p>
               It shall be just<lb/>
               as you like, &amp; if we<lb/>
               could persuade you to<lb/>
               stay here, we should<lb/>
               be only too pleased.
            </p>
            
            <closer>
               <salute>Believe me,</salute><lb/>
               <salute>Sincerely yrs.</salute><lb/>
               <signed>Helen Ilchester</signed>
            </closer>
            
            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3661_4.jpg"/>
            <note type="archival">Final page blank; shelfmark “H. 3661” in pencil.</note>
         </div>
      </body>
